text: Cleburne County is a county of the U.S. state of Arkansas. As of the 2020 census, the population was 24,711. The county seat and most populous city is Heber Springs. It was founded on February 20, 1883. == References == Category:19th-century establishments in Arkansas Category:1883 establishments in the United States Category:Arkansas counties
title: Cleburne County, Arkansas
